h2. Front-office

The TAO platform also concerns Test Takers who will have to authenticate on the platform in order to take the tests dedicated to them. In order to do that, the _Test Taker_ Class is a sub-class of the _TaoSubjectRole_ which is an instance of the _FrontOffice_ Role. Users having the _TaoSubjectRole_ may access the delivery platform.

!http://forge.taotesting.com/attachments/285/addTestTaker.png!
Fig .4
Adding a _Test Taker_ in the Test Taker Extension will create an instance of the class _Test Taker_. (_Jane_ and _John_)

!http://forge.taotesting.com/attachments/286/role-addingNewTestTaker.png!
Fig .5
You can also obviously add sub-classes of _Test Takers_ and add new properties to your own class in order to complete the description of your _Test Takers_ who will then instantiate this class. (_1StGrade_ is the class and _Nicolas_ its instance)

